<div class="postcell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
                
<p>I'm parsing HTML with regex in node.js to return a string.  However, I have been told that this is not a good idea in this post: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10005274/pull-a-specific-string-from-an-http-request-in-node-js">Pull a specific string from an HTTP request in node.js</a></p>

<p>What are the more stable alternatives? </p>

<p>I'm new to programming, so links to tutorials would be very helpful. I have trouble understanding some of the documentation explanations. </p>
    </div>

